This paper discusses distributed consensus algorithms, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also deals with the design and analysis of algorithms for distributed systems, which falls under the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper proposes a modification to the Paxos algorithm, which is widely used in distributed systems, making it relevant to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category. The paper also discusses the safety and security of the proposed algorithm, which is a topic of interest in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed algorithm, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
